text:
“owning your story is the bravest thing you will ever do” - brene brown
me in #metoo is a free drama therapy workshop for survivors of physical and emotional trauma. a closed group workshop with not more than 5-8 people that will focus on:

1. identifying and disembodying trauma as it sits in the body
2. celebrating the survivor in you 
3. embodying your strength through story-telling and psychodramas

it is important to give yourself a safe space to heal just like you have found a space to bravely express your individual stories. know someone who needs this space then do share this post with them. 
all you got to do is rsvp with us via
email: doctordramatherapy@gmail.com

venue: the little game bay
time: 6:30-8pm

text:
jury duty: fantastiska sïmon saneback, serieentreprenör och medgrundare av @wellstreetvc har tackat ja till att sitta i juryn!

sïmon är en prisbelönt entreprenör med ett brinnande intresse för innovation och socialt entreprenörskap. han har länge förespråkat en ökad jämställdhet i det svenska näringslivet och är bland annat initiativtagaren till #femtech, en ny satsning tillsammans med @tillvaxtverket, där man vill få fram fler kvinnor inom tech-industrin. 
wellstreet har på mindre än tre år gått från en startup till att bli en av mest namnkunniga spelarna inom den skandinaviska startup-scenen. nyligen meddelade bolaget lanseringen av "the factory", en 14 000 kvadratmeter glasbyggnad i sollentuna som blir nordens största innovation- och tech-hub. coolt! 
tack sïmon för att du tar plats i vår jury #nowwhathacks #metoo #wellstreet #sthlmtech

emma sheedy, miss earth guam 2018, habla sobre su experiencia en el miss earth 2018. tambien acusa a la organizacion de no hacer mucho por remover al sponsor de los eventos a pesar de las quejas presentadas de acoso sexual por una corona o clasificacion. miss earth wales 2017 & miss earth england 2017 relatan que pasaron por la misma experiencia en el miss earth 2017.  ninguna chica debería pasar por esas cosas a cambio de una corona o top!

@erma101: mi lado de la experiencia internacional de miss earth:
- después de un año y medio de preparación para mi primer concurso de belleza; en el certamen de miss earth, estaba emocionado de volver a filipinas por sexta vez. la hospitalidad de los filipinos no se encuentra en ningún otro lugar. filipinas es como un segundo hogar para mí. me uní al concurso para marcar la diferencia y ser un modelo a seguir para quienes me rodean. disfruté de la mayoría del concurso, pero lo que no sabía es que un patrocinador específico del manila yacht club cambiaría la forma en que veo el espectáculo y los patrocinadores. el patrocinador que se llama amado s. cruz se convirtió en un problema para muchos de los delegados, incluido yo mismo. para concentrarme solamente en mí mismo, me apartaron varias veces para que me invitaran a boracay, a las islas privadas y a su casa, e insistí en que yo y "las mujeres latinas bailamos para él". amado s. cruz agarró mi trasero desnudo del traje nacional. competición en la que pude alejarlo, pero me dijo constantemente que no le contara a nadie sobre ninguno de los casos.....
.

text:
i don't think words can express seeing something i produced on a woman @taranajaneen who created a movement that will go down in history. the middle spread of a magazine that is like a dream to be part of @essence 
this year especially i have buried my own personal voice in my work while i internally process my own story and journey. figuring out what i want to share and say to the world has not been easy. i know my heart creates pieces that resonate with woman from all walks of life and the jewelry for me and them represents more than external appearances. its an extension of our inner voice, our internal beauty including the hurt parts that we transform into a beautiful becoming of a healed, empowered self. the silent resonance and love i feel in my heart is so honoured for this moment. ❤ styled by @stylistjbolin (your amazing) #metoo#jewelry#manifest#voice#movement#essence#byannalay

text:
если меня спросят о то какая книга меня поразила больше всего за этот год, я отвечу: "пелевин. тайные виды на гору фудзи"
в ней прекрасно все:
- безупречный язык, который заставляет перечитывать главы кусками и целиком.
- метафоричная история, в которой сплетаются древность буддизма и современные реалии
- незримое присутствие самого пелевина с четкой авторской позицией, которую он не навязывает.
в общем, могёт современный классик, удивляет до сих пор. я бы мог петь дифирамбы еще, но кому это интересно? лучше прочтите несколько цитат)
"...ни один моисей за всю историю так и не вывел свой народ из двух последних абзацев «великого гэтсби»"
"маленькому принцу вернули наконец отжатый по беспределу астероид."
"на ней была красная майка с надписью:
#metoo
стилист нашего проекта был весельчак – в таких майках выходили на смену все уборщицы с метлами. мол, мету – работа такая."
"фестиваль русскоязычного рэпа... это как если бы с той стороны подъехали «зеленые береты» на «хаммерах» и организовали конкурс англосаксонских балалаечников."
"работу критика я еще могу понять – пересказал кое-как чужой сюжет, добавил запаха своих подмышек, и готово."
#алексбрут #смутныемысли #recommended

text:
“owning your story is the bravest thing you will ever do” - brene brown
me in #metoo is a free drama therapy workshop for survivors of physical and emotional trauma. a closed group workshop with not more than 5-8 people that will focus on:

1. identifying and disembodying trauma as it sits in the body
2. celebrating the survivor in you 
3. embodying your strength through story-telling and psychodramas

it is important to give yourself a safe space to heal just like you have found a space to bravely express your individual stories. know someone who needs this space then do share this post with them. 
all you got to do is dm us @doctordramatherapy or rsvp with us via
email: doctordramatherapy@gmail.com

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

normförskjutning pågår. den svenska metoo-rörelsen samlar tankarna inför årsdagen av skådespelarnas manifest och startskott, #tystnadtagning.
inför ettårsdagen av #tystnadtagning, de svenska skådespelarnas metooupprop, som är i morgon 9 november, bjöd kultur- och demokratiminister alice bah kuhnke (mp) in till ett seminarium tidigare i veckan i riksdagshuset under rubriken #metoo – ett år senare, nu tar vi nästa steg.
på bilden ser du emmy lilliehorn, alán ali, ulrika hyllert, alice bah kuhnke och eva röse. #nomaste #tystnadtagning

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
have you ever wondered what a gender equal world would be like? in july 2018, @theeconomist published a fascinating article entitled “if 50% of ceos were women, generation xx: january 2069”. on this episode, we're imagining for a moment that gender equality is the norm. women are advancing in corporations at the same rate and hold just as many powerful positions as men. this weeks #sheinnovatespodcast features sacha nauta, public policy editor for the economist, joins us to explore this world and together we try to answer the question: what got us to a gender equal future?
for more stories like please sign up to @the___fix our weekly newsletter for an exclusive dose of insights, events and stories from women (and men) passionate about creating a gender equal world all: michellepking.com/thefix

text:
it’s the last day to join us in whole woman.
::
if any part of you feels like your life isn’t really yours, or that you’ve cut off parts of yourself in order to fit into a box or not rock the boat, it is so important to me that you know that your life doesn’t have to feel this way.
::
whole woman closes at 11:59pm et tonight, 11/5/18. today is the last day to join. to learn more if whole woman is a fit for you go to http://wholewoman.me (link in profile).
::
sidelining women’s needs and full expression has been the silent killer of our time. stuffing down who we are leads to addiction, disease, and lack of leadership in positions that guide our culture. there’s a reason we are experiencing things like the #metoo campaign, ferocity about getting to the polls tomorrow, and seeing more openness about spirituality on social media. we are experiencing an opening. there’s a wave of bravery, of anger, of women finally standing up and demanding the freedom to be ourselves without being told we’re too outspoken, weird, or selfish.
::
i’m inviting you to step into this opening and explore what it means for you to be the real you. you may go into the depths of your soul and discover that you’ve been hiding parts of yourself that want - no, need - to come out.
::
whole woman is a sanctuary for you to step out from the pressures and rules of your life and have the space, safety, and guidance to explore who you are and what you truly want. for your invitation go to http://wholewoman.me.
::
have a question about whole woman and if it’s right for you? join me on instagram live today at 1pm et. see you there! video by pearson jenks

text:
rp @vegan_vizard the milk from the much promoted “glass and half” does not come from cows grazing in some peaceful idyl in fields of buttercups, with the sun warming their backs and their calves by their sides, in most cases nothing could be further from the truth.

two or three times every day, dairy cows are hooked up to milk machines. they are commonly pushed to produce ten times more milk than is natural.”
like other factory farmed animals the lot of a cow is a life filled with suffering and exploitation in dreadful conditions.
the dairy cow is kept constantly pregnant in a continuous and exhausting cycle of misery. within two to three months of giving birth cows are impregnated again, mostly by artificial insemination. as lactation lasts around 10 months the cow is simultaneously pregnant and lactating for 6 to 8 months during each calving cycle. cows have a 6 to 8 week period between lactation ceasing and their next calving.
in order to provide you with milk,  a food that we like every other mammal no longer needs after weaning, she is milked two or three times each day and often much more frequently. after giving birth her calf is taken away within twenty-four hours after the calf has taken the colostrum, which in all animals protects the young one from disease. however the calf is removed before he or she can have any of the milk which must all be kept for humans, a calf never has any of his or her mother’s milk.

what happens to her calf? if he is male he is considered an unwanted by product of the dairy industry and unless he is required for breeding he is shot after barely a week of life.

text:

text:
so this is my big reveal. i’ve joined with a friend, ex buyer colleague to set up an e-commerce fashion business @bellaunica_xx between us we’ve got 40 years experience of working with top 10 fashion retailers but combining this demanding career with a family has not been easy. mums,like immigrants, sometimes have to become entrepreneurs because the traditional workplace can be hostile or unaccommodating even when employers pay lip service to diversity. i’ve signed two ndas in my life that are all in the spotlight now for #metoo but i’ve no regrets. i rose pretty high but hit the glass ceiling hard and being divorced and part time didn’t help. i got to the stage where it was men all the way up and women all the way down. fashion retail buying offices are still entrenched with 80s/90s ideas of presenteeism under the surface. working for men with stay at home wives and no idea what you might have to handle ...or worse women with no kids and/or no empathy. i hung on to a modicum of part time and ran the gauntlet of tutting colleagues but despite considerable commercial success it all got too much. so i’ve been on a long period of garden leave and now i’m free and i’m going to try to work for me. to keep the lawyers happy i will keep this anonymous. if you do know my name or where i worked please don’t mention it in your lovely comments. support, likes, follows and purchases 😃are all very welcome. 20% off at checkout with discount code for my followers ciao20 
please help me not have to go back to the grind and pretending i can give my soul to a company and not see my kids. i’ve got a year to make this work. wish me luck ❤️💋🤞 x

text:
i was raised in a conservative way, in a family in which girls were judged by the way they dressed, or how they behaved at parties. 
i have always been aware that sexism is definitely a problem in society; it is still present in our everyday life. girls are still slut shamed and women do not receive equal rights as men do.

daily, i hear stories told by my friends or any other national news where women are raped and murdered, every single day. i know this is a sensitive topic, and i know a lot has been made to stop this phenomenon. still, we should be aware every single day as well, we should stand for what we believe, for equality.

do simple things like stop slut shaming on a conversation with your male friends. there are small actions that eventually can make big changes. 
for example, i told my cousin that he should listen to emma watson’s speech, the one she gave for the “he for she” movement and he did. he told me he now understood a little bit more feminism and why it was so important to me and to every woman in the world. it is a small action, but he told one of his friends that used to judge girls, and maybe that friend told another friend and that’s the way we can change the world.

i just feel like we should never forget that every human deserves fundamental rights and to be treated with respect and dignity. but it is more important to act.

remember that your opinion will not change the world, but your actions will.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

assume your attacker is bigger, stronger, and more skilled.  let me tell you, yes, a larger opponent is much harder to deal with...is that an end all?  no!  all attributes matter.  speed, cardio, agility... the list goes on.  at ekm we teach you a long extensive list of attributes, how to fight with an injury, awareness, and tactics.  we can learn from everyone.  therefore we encourage you touch hands with as many people as possible throughout your training.  this is why beginners are encouraged.  that’s right, we want to train with a fresh person.  welcome to our play ground, our current students cannot wait to show you what they have learned so far. .
.

text:
more videos from yesterday's ministration at @ignitegla .

we need to break out from stronghold we have built by ourselves and for ourselves that are hindering us.
.

we need to break out from the crazy to quickly define who we are without accurate revelation, the pressure to quickly explain our seasons when you don't even fully comprehend it, the pride that comes with titles which sometimes limits us to be more &do more.
.

we need to break out from the pressure to "make sense to man". this not to say we get up to do ridiculous things that are not in line with scriptures, nooooooo but darling, sometimes or most times, god's instructions don't make sense if you look at it through human eyes but it done break his word or grieve the holy spirit. people won't always approve of your journey or process.just be sure its god, be accountable to god & the people/authority god has placed in your life and keep moving. accountability is necessary but different from being controlled or manipulated. .

stop looking back to "egypt" stay focused to god's party for you. we need to break free from the temptation to return to egypt or things god has delivered us from. .

we need to break free from the temptation to compare ourselves to one another. when the thought comes, shut it down by starving it &remain grounded in the word.
.

we need to break free from the zone of "wishful thinking" and actually move into the realm of faith. faith calls forth those things that be not like they were. faith takes actions & speaks boldly. faith doesn't wait to see before celebrating. faith is joy zone. this is different from the attitude of, "if god likes he will do it" don't treat your destiny this way. fight the good fight of faith.
.

break out of anxiety and learn to rest in the lord, in his word and in what he has done & what he is doing. rest is not the same thing as passiveness. rest is a posture of trust and it isn't necessarily "in action". sometimes, he could ask you to do nothing and sometimes he can ask you to engage but whatever the case might be, always function from the place of rest. .

don't let anything stop you, not even pain, lies or the devil... break out!!! #ispeak

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i have a fire in my belly tonight.  i've spent too much of my life being afraid of what people think.  when i was looking for help i was met by being told i'm imagining it, it didn't happen, it's not true.  like many i'm part of the #metoo.  i won't even try and go into the sad things that happened in my youth as it would take too long. but i want to share one story. 
in high school i lost my hair after extreme trauma, depression, anxiety and insomnia.  i was told for 6 months that it was my imagination or if i stopped worrying about it would get better.  it didn't, it got worse and it was a major blow to my self esteem.  i became even more impaired. it happened again after my nephew, who i helped raise, killed himself.  i could go on but i won't. i do want to say in hopes this is heard, if even only by a couple.  and dammit, i'm getting my power back.  people didn't like me when i worried about it, might as well stop worrying. here is my proposition: if someone says they are not well, believe them. if someone deals with chronic illness no need to tell them they are in it because they enjoy being ill.  if someone is grieving, don't tell them they are in self pity.  if they are not well in the mind, that is still the body and we all have different abilities and constitutions.  if someone says they are hurting, accept it. if someone says they are suicidal,  take it seriously.  and if you can't do that, then at least leave that person alone. it already sucks feeling bad, we don't need to shame people as well. 
#metoo #idontcare #divinegoddess #empowerment #youarebeautiful #yesitakevitaminsandnotheywontfixitdammit
#italreadysucksfeelingbad

text: this record was probably ducktails’ best record to date. the epitome of sleepy, groovy and nostalgic music to study, road trip and bicycle to; it’s not revolutionary- it’s just great comfort food. sadly, controversy mired the release and the record was virtually shelved. i spoke with matt on twitter,  after he seemingly removed himself from the internet entirely during the indie media circus surrounding his mistreatment of women, and he seemed incredibly shocked by the allegations sent his way. his entire career as a musician was set ablaze, whether for good or bad. what’s sadder is that the truth is something only he and the alleged victims of his mistreatment can know. interestingly, his case and public hanging was eerily reminiscent of that of aziz ansari, who was also accused with what essentially amounted to being a shitty date- an example of the dangers of toxic masculinity and male privilege, sure, but a far cry from sexual assault or anything close to it. there have been many innocent people (among the many guilty) who deserve a redemption arc, but ultimately never get one. it may not be what you want, but we cannot simply commit trial by fire as the public, destroying and “cancelling” people with only rumors as evidence. the same thing happened to conor oberst (bright eyes) and the accusations were eventually proven to be entirely false- an actual ploy to destroy the man by a strange women he never even met. witch hunts in any capacity serve no greater purpose and it would do society well to remember that it is a nightmare if (or when) those same pitchforks are pointed toward you. #jerseydevil #ducktails #metoo #citationplease #azizansari

text:
met de billen bloot

net fijn gebeld met een man die misschien online mee wil reizen met mij met de sacred union retreat (of toch misschien zelf in het diepe springt met de retraite van yama! want er zijn nog een paar plekjes en dat is natuurlijk duizend maal transformerender voor wie het durft!) maar als je niet durft/kan/wil, mag je dus volgen hoe ik door mijn shit heen wroet en antwoorden zoek op mijn liefdeslevensvragen. als een soort soap krijg je een kijkje in de keuken van mijn liefdesleven. “de man in kwestie” zal hier en daar ook wel een mannelijk perspectief geven in de facebook groep vermoed ik. (dwz “mijn” geliefde die mee gaat naar de retreat). ben je een ietsipietsy verslaafd aan liefde, zoek je het allemaal buiten jezelf, ben je bang dat je geliefde je verlaat, verlies je je totaal in relaties, neiging tot symbiose, kun je maar niet stoppen met manipuleren en spelletjes spelen, herhaal je steeds dezelfde drama in je relaties, heb je allemaal toffe ego strategieën ontwikkeld die je pseudo liefde geven maar je niet echt ten diepste gelukkig maken, jaag je je geliefden bij je weg, geniet je niet van seks, ben je benieuwd wat seks nu echt heilig maakt, ben je benieuwd hoe man en vrouw in harmonie samen kunnen leven zonder de spanning te verliezen, kun je je niet binden in een relatie, heb je ondanks alle dearmoring nog steeds pijn in je yoni en wil je weten hoe je jouw seks nu voor eens en voor altijd kunt genezen? wil je je ouders nog dieper en oprechter kunnen liefhebben? heb je vroeger van alles gemist en ben je daarom zo fucked up in de liefde? heb je het gevoel dat je niet alleen je eigen shit zit op te ruimen, maar dat er systemisch/collectief van alles door jou heen beweegt? heb je je hele leven het gevoel seksueel misbruikt te zijn zonder aanwijsbare reden en wil je helderheid? wil je voorbij dader- en slachtofferschap een bijdrage zijn aan de genezing van #metoo? wil je een bijdrage zijn aan de collectieve shift van heling tussen mannen en vrouwen. geloof jij ook in een wereld waarin mannen en vrouwen in harmonie samenleven, ieder vanuit zijn/haar eigen unieke essentie, waar ieder mens vrij is om zijn/ haar potentie te ontwikkelen?>>>

text:
“i had a dog called tuffy — we named him that after watching hum aapke hain koun. he was brown and he used to jump so high... then dude happened, when we were adults. dude is a labrador, and he was gifted to us.” “the #metoo movement has empowered women to tell their stories; it has empowered them to not feel shame anymore. your workplace should be your second safe space, after your home. when there’s no respect from your colleagues, it’s just so sad,” “i got to know that a lot of animals, especially horses, donkeys and dogs, are put down when they are no longer required. it makes me so emotional. where do they go? especially for bigger animals like horses, it’s very difficult to get that kind of an establishment.” “marriage doesn’t feel different. @virat.kohli and i have been working around the clock, we hardly spend time together, we both have very hectic lives. so, we are living in a house and we have spent barely any time in it. for us, home is, like, wow! it’s a vacation,” “i didn’t grow up dreaming to become an actor. it seemed extremely improbable that i would make a mark here, because i was growing up in bangalore. in a way, people there were a little snooty towards hindi films, and my friends and i were too,” reveals @anushkasharma. 📸: @prasadnaaik
👗: @rahulvijay1988
💁: @mrudul.pathak
💇: @yiannitsapatori/ @fazemanagement
👩‍🎨: @puneetbsaini
assisted by: @akshitas11, @divyagursahani, @kavishaa_k (styling)
📝: @rajeevmasand
.
note: no animals were harmed in the production of this cover. bailey, an adopted stray, participated in this shoot with the full knowledge and cooperation of her owners. 🐶

text:
happy diwali week everyone! today the country celebrates dhanteras and we in goa, are celebrating eve of narak chaturdashi , when the city is flooded with creativity . 
do check out our very own mini narakasur inspired by the #metoo movement. this is the fourth year we are making narakasur and having our annual diwali party. all the behind the scenes on my insta stories ( also fb stories) for those who follow me on fb. so much more as the evening goes on ! almost all pictures will be on stories. do check out my blog post on the previous years narakasurs and why i love the celebration . link in bio .#narakchaturdashi #narakasura #diwali . and now about the fruit platter 😊 it’s the perfect way to kick start this week, we had a lovely time @kenilworthgoa thanks to @bubblemiri , the feta and watermelon sandwiches were a revelation! have a safe and healthy-ish diwali 😁

text:
"a woman at a certain age who is unmarried, our society teaches her to see it as a deep personal failure. and a man, after a certain age isn't married, we just think he hasn't come around to making his pick"
📚
the only book that i managed to finish in october is "we should all be feminists" by chimamanda ngozi adichie. this book is a gem and must be read by as many people as possible. it spoke to me on so many levels. i've not related to a book so much in a long time. adichie talks about things that we shy away from talking in our lives or just ignore them by calling them "normal". it is about time that we start eliminating these supposedly small "normal" things that discriminate on the basis of gender. it is so frustrating when such things happen. a couple of months back i went out with my friends for dinner and at the end of the meal, i handed out my card to the waiter for billing. and guess what? he turned to one of the guys in the group to enter the pin. i ignored it and took the machine instead and entered the pin. and there he goes again, giving the card back to the guy. why is it so ingrained in our minds that a guy is supposed to pay bills? why do the waiters in a restaurant still turn to the guy when the girl is handing out the card for payment? i would really like to be able to go to a restaurant and not be treated like this. this book gave me hope that may be people who read it, will change and slowly but steadily we will eventually get closer to equality.
📚
qotd: have you had any incidents like this which made you feel that we are still miles away from equality?
📚

text:
the #metoo has become a powerful and impactful campaign for showing the prevalence of a problem experienced by far too many people, a majority of them women. #metoo is about accountability from the people who don’t bat an eyelash about catcalling a stranger on the street or touching someone without that person’s consent.
#metoo is about showing the human face of a problem but more than that, it’s a demand that men #dobetter. the #metoo movement is more than women sharing their stories of assault, it’s about giving them value in the society, it’s about finally realizing that times up, it’s about letting women know that their voice matters and that that their assault was not their fault. it’s about giving power to the women. this one year old movement has brought to the eyes of the audience the reality of so called influencers who were abusers, molesters and rapists. this movement has reiterated the magnitude and intensity of assault against victims around the world. i want to congratulate every woman who has shared their story and i encourage other women to do the same. #timesup
(🎨- @curious_lauren )

text:
over the weekend i have the pleasure of attending the calendar launch of the strong woman project with my daughter. 
@aliciafistonich created this project to celebrate  already strong women and encourage other women to enter the gym and lift weights without fear of judgement or expectation. with the aim to decompartmentalise the sexual objectification of the fitness industry as it currently stands and encourage all women to get fit and healthy to better themselves. 
she has also aligned herself with the charity friends with dignity who helps women and children rebuild their lives after domestic violence. i could not think of a better fit. 
for those that have followed me for a long time will attest to my constant iteration for healthy body, healthy mind. strong body, strong mind. when your core foundation is maintaining wellness on all levels, you are better equipped to deal with the challenges that life throws before you.

in rehab i was advised by my psychologist that “exercising might be a good idea”. i don’t know that there has ever been a more pertinent piece of advice given to me. 
thank you to the women that shared their triumphs over adversity on the day. 
for every story told we are opening the door for another woman to breathe a little easier. yes unfortunately #metoo

the calendar is spectacular and features real life relatable strong women. @jillwescombe what an astonishing job you have done of portraying these super heroes in all their glory. it is available from the website link below and all proceeds go to friends with dignity. 
so lovely to meet you all and thankyou for creating another community where women can be empowered to be anything they want to be. 
https://www.thestrongwomanproject.com/

#thestrongwomanproject @friendswithdignity #womensupportingwomen #fitwomen #fitlife #mentalhealthawareness #domesticviolenceawareness

text:
642 things to draw: 125
_____________________
i love and hate our generation. i suppose i am a bit arbitrary. i will support anything inclusive lgbtq+s say because we generally tend not to, you know, prohibit certain human rights from others, like they do to us. what i hate about our generation (and people as a whole, actually) is those who refuse to believe what we say.
_____________________
i hate not being believed. i didn’t really have a problem until the last year or so, which may have been influenced by the #metoo movement. i felt stupid, as someone who doesn’t really feel comfortable using male or female pronouns about themselves but sometimes slips because i’ve had a lifetime of assumptions (both male and female). i felt like it wasn’t my place to let people know that yes, i’ve been sexually harassed and assaulted in my time. (i hate the term ‘sexually’ because for me, there was nothing sexual about it). my issue is that the most recent time i told someone “i’ve been assaulted” they laughed and said “no you haven’t”.
_____________________
as though i don’t exist, i’m often not listened to. like a cartoon ghost, screaming words or pleas for understanding and other people just beat on, careless. i frequently have to try to convey the fact that as a queer person i am not safe like straight people are (“look at the fucking statistics!”, i want to scream). i do not have the privilege of walking down a street holding a man’s hand. when i meet some people i am caricaturised as a ‘gbf’ or the ‘catty gay’ (et al the stereotypes) before i’ve said a word. i cannot give blood. i can’t get married in most countries. in most of the world i am robbed of basic human rights because i am seen as something irreligious, freakish and disgusting. the worst part is that still, in the uk, i’m told that “most people don’t think that way about queer people”. not being believed is a form of gaslighting. it whitewashes the struggles of the queer (and female, if we’re talking about #metoo also) community. what i wouldn’t give for men (and i clearly mean straight, white ones) to live a year in my shoes and see that we are still oppressed. i thought i was still a human being.

text:
i just wanted to say a huge thank to you all for your support with my new book don’t hold back. i never set out to be a published author, i only ever wanted to be a dancer...! have you read don’t hold back? i hope it was or is worth the journey!

we are building up our reviews and hope you might also be able to write a review to continue encouraging readers to take a dive in. 
my message is clear, i want to give people hope, help them face their fears, build a positive life around them, and discover their truth and new opportunities.

i would really appreciate it if you could support me on writing a review and that you enjoyed the read and have been inspired.

to write a review please visit the amazon page (link below) don't hold back https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/1999584945/ref=cm_sw_r_cp_api_sl.3bbk4zh2ry and then scroll down to write a review, see picture. 
thank you in advance,

love and light,

emma-jane xx

debosmita shared valuable insights and best practices amongst a distinguished list of panelists and a thoughtful audience.

text:
si me seguís en las redes sociales seguramente estéis hartos de escucharme hablar de que me molesta el machismo, la lgtbfobia, la xenofobia, el racismo y cualquier odio (sobre todo hacia las minorías). esta vez vengo a hablar de otra cosa distinta, que también me molesta bastante. me queda algo más de medio año para cumplir los 30 y tanto a mí como a mis amigas ya nos ha caído la pregunta “¿por qué están solas?”. ¿solas? ¿quieren que les recite mi árbol genealógico o empiezo por los amigos que mantengo desde la infancia? claramente, esas personas necesitan visitar al ocultista (urgentemente). dentro de este marco temático hay algo que sigue molestándome como esa pequeña piedrecita en el zapato, que al principio no le das importancia pero tras un largo trayecto te quitas la bota, el calcetín y lo que haga falta estés dónde estes para quitar la maldita chinita. 
hay muchas personas que se creen con la necesidad de aconsejarte sobre tu relaciones. no de una forma constructiva, más bien metiendo las narices en un tema que desconocen absolutamente. y ahí, empieza mi rabia.
¿por qué nos metemos en las relaciones de los demás aun sabiendo que cada relación es distinta? es decir, todos hemos metido la pata alguna vez, a todos nos han hecho daño o incluso lo hemos hecho nosotros. 
la relaciones cada vez son menos lineales porque los seres humanos nos volvemos más exigentes con nuestras parejas, sobre todo las mujeres que antes aceptaban sin más lo que “les tocaba” por falta de protección y educación, y eso forma parte de la evolución social.
no entiendo si ninguna relación es perfecta porqué nos empeñamos en querer que las de nuestro alrededor lo sean.
ofrecer ayuda y consejos es maravilloso, pero hasta el punto de respetar las decisiones y la privacidad de las otras personas.

y antes de juzgar, por favor, mírense el ombligo. 
ah, y si no han pedido su opinión. quizá es que no la quieren.

text:
personal training with kaustav sehgal!

kaustav has trained under some of the world’s leading krav maga experts including amnon darsa, avi moyal, avshalom dahan and eyal yanilov.

he is one of few instructors who can trace the lineage of his training directly back to imi lichtenfeld, the founder of krav maga. in addition to being a senior civilian instructor, kaustav holds numerous certifications in:
▪taekwondo
▪mixed martial arts & krav maga
▪vip protection
▪russian kettlebell training
▪kids' krav maga
▪functional fitness training ​kaustav’s varied clientele include well known names in the field of industry and entertainment such as :
▪trained rani mukherjee for her role as an expert hand to hand combatant in the movie mardaani.
▪arjun wallia (wallsons group , securitas india)
▪ashok masti (musician)
▪sahil bhatia (baani group)

text:
"this is what is radical about this movement – the long overdue objectivity that is now being given to the lived experiences of women, specifically lived experiences with sexual violence. for centuries, the narratives of women in india have been discarded and unrecognised. 
our patriarchal society denied the rights of objectivity to the stories of women who are often relegated to the realm of spirituality and domesticity and thus deemed as irrational. our voices, our narratives have been hindered from entering the public sphere and are thus not considered in making policies that directly affect us like policies surrounding sexual assault.

burke's speech made me realise that the allowance of rape culture in private life i.e through your home, friendships etc allow public structures of oppression to go unnoticed." click the link in our bio to read the full story.

text:
я вчера прошляпила пост =р
это оказалось не так то легко, воспоминаний много, все разные, сумбурные, таймлапс вообще страдает *рукалицо* 
но я не сдала на попятную, нетнетнет :)
компановка и облагораживание мыслей идёт во всю, посты печатаются, сохраняются, но дополняются, перепечатываются, цензура накладывается, потом снова убирается... *выдох* нелегко в общем.
да и иллюстрацию каждый день нарисовать для себя это надо исхитриться. абы как не хочется, эта идея #7днейвоспоминаний очень важна для меня, я вынашивала её несколько месяцев; первые шаги всегда неровные, а блины комом, но всё же, у меня желание сделать это максимально красиво, как я только смогу. 
если у вас есть что сказать "за" или "против" моей идеи, говорите сейчас, мне очень интересно.

text:
makeup? or make her up? today you can take a selfie and fix your face till it's just right for how society says your face should look. and most of the time it's us men demanding such looks or standards that a woman has to achieve to flatter our stupid male ego. a woman has to hide behind layers today of paint and hair products because that's what society says is beautiful. i think makeup is amazing but whenever makeup is your go to for hiding the pain and the hurt of not feeling beautiful that's horrible.
.
 as we peel away the false nature of what the media tells a little girl what beauty is. let's show her that she is beautiful as she is without compromise, that what makes her beautiful is her soul and her heart. not the smokey eyes or the photoshopped skin tones or the fantastic lipstick. remind your daughter, your sister or your friend that she is beautiful no matter what. and if you need to be reminded to tell your lover as well you need to jump off a cliff because you need to tell her everyday that she's the most beautiful object of your affection. that's right, men...listen up.

text:
no woman actively looks forward to getting her period. even after decades of menstruating, it can be a painful, expensive hassle every month that leaves you feeling completely flattened. but if you're a woman living on the street, having a period isn't a hassle...it's a nightmare! because if you can't muddle together enough money for food or shelter, it is unlikely you'll be able to afford sanitary towels or tampons.

#thehomelessperiod believes that tampons and towels should be made available through homeless shelters, the same way the government provides condoms. find out more on thehomelessperiod.com 🔴🚺👭🗣#yoursistersspace

text:
relaxing weekend with minecraft and lazing around. pain hasn’t been kind to me. i’m hoping to start selling some of my leftover art from before basic training, soon. i’d love to raise money to get this tattoo, i just need to be able to focus and work... it’s a very important tattoo for me and i’d really like to meet my goal of extra money so i can get it before the end of the year. the lotus represents purity, detachment, and something that is beautiful that rises through the muddy waters. the dragonfly represents embracing change and seeing it as positive and freeing. it represents strength, joy and bravery. the dragonfly is a creature of both the water and the air. the air in dragonfly tattoo designs signifies freedom. the breaking geometric shapes on the dragonfly is because i’m not all the way there yet, it’s still more of a goal than a reality. the lines in the background that tie the piece together is now recognized as the sexual assault survivor symbol, a rose on fire. "it is a unity symbol inspired by the loops of our dna structure and our universal infinity sign. it combines inspiration from lady gaga's favorite flower – the white rose – to breathe life into an organic and growing symbol.

the final image embraces a fiery shape to give us power and strength everywhere we go." #tattoodssign #art #artist #smallbusiness #painting #drawing #sketching #sexualassault #survivor #lotus #dragonfly #ladygaga #firerose #unitysurvivor #ladygaga #metoo @ladygaga @kerbyrosanes  @lostconversations

text: i just wanted to say how important it is to take care of yourself first. you can’t fill from an empty cup and to take care of others you need to take care of yourself first. i’ve been thinking about this for a while and have begun to practice it in my daily life with one of my friends who i feel can sometimes be too much for me. i love her so much and i know i can still be friends with her, but i want to work on knowing myself first. just my thoughts for today... -rissy ❤️ #love #youareenough #loveyourselffirst #quotes #quotesdaily #inspiration #sexualassault #empowerment  #survivor #metoo #metoomovement #recovery #feminist #feminism #feministquote  #trauma #female #inspirationalquote #equality #trigger #triggerwarning #assault #ptsd #mybodymychoice #consent #endrapeculture #timesup #depression #anxiety

text:
day 307. good fucking question, witches. because we can’t fucking work it out:
“in the county court last week a melbourne man admitted to raping three women and indecently assaulting a fourth. it was an emotional moment for him. he dabbed his eyes with a tissue. and then, after pleading guilty – essentially owning up to being a serial rapist – glenn antony hartland, or ‘dylan”’as he was known on the dating app tinder, walked out of court.”
https://www.theage.com.au/national/victoria/tinder-rapist-admits-guilt-walks-free-until-sentencing-20181101-p50dbh.html

police aren’t talking about why this fuckstick is free, but we assume they opposed bail. yet a dangerous rapist with priors is free right now to attack other women. 
we assume this man will stay in melbourne so only women in that city need be frightened of him, but who the fuck knows? he’s breached bail before, so could turn up anywhere. why the freaking fuck should women have to be scared? why the fuck is a confessed rapist free? just what in the ever-loving fuck is going on?

like and share, witches. women (and men) need to see this creep’s face. need to know what he looks like. need to keep the fuck away from him and ensure their friends and family do too. 
what is our court system even for? and why aren’t crimes against women taken seriously? 
#witchesbeangry

#lockhimup

text:
alot of people use their power over people to talk about things like political stands, equality, importance, and for a while now it's circling around the #metoo.

don't get me wrong, these are all really important topics and everyone needs to be in line and aware with all these depressions in the world.

my problem is that, everybody is talking about it.. literally everyone.. which is like, surrounding yourself in an extremely thick, warm, furry blanket in the mid summer heat. and then you will poke your feet out before eventually just ripping the blanket off, because everyone has a breaking point. so i'm here to help. 
i make it a mission to remind people to be happy, and i can list them a bunch of reasons and thoughts why they need to just rip that blanket of negativity off. because i understand everybody has their own fair share of negative retaliations, and their down pours, i believe that if i used my time with them no matter how long or short it maybe, i can give them a breath of fresh, cold, and comforting air.

that's all i want to be right now.

let me know if i have ever made you feel better, by just being me!

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
persephone’s dancer rising (base only)
hand-carved alabaster stone

even more progress... and more... and more... and more and more... her face is beginning to shape and state back.

this part of the piece, the base, is a conglomeration of ancient goddess forms from throughout our ancestral past, rising up to hold the phoenix wing aloft. 
in process, a few more details and i have only 5 more days to go. 
this piece is meant as a trophy of triumph, a modern nike, presented to all women who have endured, (silently, painfully, sometimes with strength, other times with weakness, always courageously, and always without expressed informed consent) sexual assault.
it represents your futures beyond this era (that could end tomorrow or next year but certainly within your lifetime). it is the triumph that is inevitable for all women.

text:
just found this piece i wrote 3 years ago - here unedited:
what comes next is quite personal and i'm not sure how i feel about writing this. i do know however how many of us are struggling or have struggled in similar ways, so i may as well throw it out there. feel free to share your thoughts with me.

as a woman i live in a world that teaches me women's bodies are meant to be perfect, youthful and above all skinny. growing up, it's always felt normal to feel 'not good enough', not skinny enough the way i was. as a 14 year old, i froze my way through winter, refusing to wear a proper jacket for the fear of looking fat. as an 17 year old i'd starved myself periodically to lose weight: not eating for a day here, an afternoon there was normal, dieting became second nature. 
as a 24 year old i started running to burn calories hoping for the scale to drop below that magic mark that promised a better me. most attempts failed, i'd stick to my new routine for a little while, only to stuff my face after with 5 mayonnaise-drowned tuna sandwiches the next moment and go back to not liking myself. i'm lucky it never spiralled into an episode of anorexia or bulimia but i have a few girlfriends for who it did. losing weight was an imperative even when i was my skinniest.

the world around me though always felt like it was teaching me that food was bad - and so i treated it as such.

in 2012 i challenged myself to get 'the perfect body' once and for all. australia is a place of bikini bodies as far as your eyes can see and living in manly beach didn't make it easier. i started training like a maniac: 6am bootcamps on the beach, tough mudders, running, soccer, boxing, cross fit, yoga, pilates - you name it, i did it. i read every blog i could get my hands on, started obsessively doing, eating, reading everything you can do to be healthy: i filtered my water, i made smoothies, glutenfree cakes; i ditched the dairy, the gluten, the sugar, the alcohol, the smoking, the red meat, the processed foods. continued in comments

text:
molested from the age of 5-8yrs old - raped in my late 20's- i once had a family member spit in my face as they accused me of wasting toilet paper - a man i loved used to call me names and cuss me out in public whenever i had my head up accusing me of checking out every man that walked by - this same man looked me in the eye as he broke my thumb - the only bone i have ever had break was broken by a man who said he "loved" me - a 6'4" man once pulled a knife out on me when i found things of my family members' that my boyfriend at the time was being accused of stealing in his stuff and confronted him about it -- at the age of 2 i was taken from my mom by cps and put into a foster family home because she had moved me away from a fight between her and her abusive boyfriend at the time and i fell  and hit my eye on the corner of a table -the sister my mom had with this man i have not seen since - id have a 12 year old by now however when i called my boyfriend on the way to get an abortion and told him i didn't want to he told me i better; he didn't want anything to do with me or the baby -fear won that day and i proceeded and part of me died on that table that day - 
i understand hate - i understand feeling worthless - i understand not wanting to live or participate in life -- i know what it feels like to be betrayed by your own blood - i know what it feels like to feel alone - i know darkness - i know how it feels to carry shame and guilt and self hate --i know how it feels to feel ugly and want to rip your own skin off - i know how it feels to not know who you can trust -  i also know the power of the spirit - how resilient it is - how every time my heart broke it grew back stronger - how no matter what i have faced and experienced i stand strong - i can still create beauty despite all the ugliness i have been through -- i can still smile through the tears - and all these things that could have easily broken me; turned me cold, actually made my heart birth more compassion and empathy - made me love more not less- 
i love what i do - i love when someone sits with me and they may not be in the best mood or they may be experiencing something in their life

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text_retweet:
ten years ago today! from our long time supporter @kristinbauer 😊✊❤️
・・・
remember this moment? i cried tears of joy on that day. we really did something great together and america benefited because we showed up! this tuesday lets show up and vote and change the course of history! repost from @barackobama - as i reflect on election night ten years ago today, i can’t help but think about where my political career started. i wasn’t running for office. i was running a voter-registration drive in chicago. what i learned then -- and what would become the premise of my 2008 campaign -- was that you couldn't just fight for existing votes. you had to reach out to all of these people who had lost faith and lost trust, and get them off the sidelines.

so during our first campaign, when i started seeing all these stories about record turnout in communities all over the country -- from young people in line for hours in iowa to elderly folks in lawn chairs down in florida -- i knew that we had shown what is possible when everybody decides to participate. and that, in and of itself, gave people a sense of their own power -- their own agency in the kind of country we want to leave for our kids. when more people get off the sidelines and decide to participate, our country becomes a little more representative of its people -- of everyone's collective decision. and american politics can change as a result.

so on election day this tuesday, i’m not just asking you to vote. i'm asking you to really show up once again. talk with your friends, convince some new voters, and get them out to vote because then something powerful happens. change happens. hope happens. and with each new step we take in the direction of fairness, and justice, and equality, and opportunity, hope spreads.

newest piece! these are two collages that i made from magazines, newspaper and scrapbook paper. the first piece is more political than the second piece, but there are hints in the second piece. the second piece is more about culture in america. this piece is so political because as i was cutting up these pieces from the papers, certain words screamed political to me. the first piece was done on watercolor paper with a watercolor wash and the second piece was done on drawing paper. let me know what you think! text_retweet:
here is the comic in its long form, shortened version to fit instagram's 10 image slider.  made by @wanderingghandss ------------------------------ #repost @therestlessquill
・・・
here's a story about a sexual harasser, mohan polamar, who is also a yoga teacher. oh the access. 
this is the couple who runs the practice room @thepracticeroomdotin in wheeler road, bangalore. 
the women whom he harassed got together and created this comic.

when the women complained, the practice room put together a committee. this included the harasser's wife who also runs the place along with the harasser. 
there was flat out denial, gaslighting and aggression.  the women were told the complaint would be entertained only if there were more than 10 women who complained. when the women insisted, he was asked to take time off. but a month later he's back to teaching, having "reflected deeply." and then, the cleverest cut of all. the husband and wife duo have coopted this comic to circulate this among their classes claiming what a great illustration of how not to behave as a yoga teacher.

#metooindia
#metoo

#meetoo
#metooindia 
#metooyoga

text:
yo guys i want to thank everyone for the support i've been receiving all day. i feel as tho a weight i've been carrying for years has finally been lifted off my back and i wasn't even carrying it for myself. it's a very scary thing to put your trauma/life out for the world to know and see and a majority of people won't or are not confident enough to publicly address their abusers and they have every right to feel that way. again i want to say #youarenotalone i know it's scary and i know its hard to even tell your closest friends but we as a generation and a community have to address these problems and hold #accountability and #truth at the utmost importance in these times. 
the idea of a relationship to me has never been about facing the world or your demons together but to know that you don't have to do it alone.

if you ever find yourself in a situation with a person you hold close to your heart threating you, manipulating you, or actually psychically/mentally harming you please recognize #abuse and get the hell out!! they are never going to be worth your time and they obviously don't hold you to the stature that they should be or did at some point. #metoo #metoomovement

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green, author
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
while root and bone pays homage to traditional recipes of the south, dishes are elevated with conscientiously-sourced ingredients and the occasional modern twist. take for example the “drunken deviled eggs”; a pink version of the original topped with pickled beets, fresh herbs and root chips. 
the masterminds behind what is arguably one of nyc’s most beloved southern joints? janine booth and her husband jeff mcinnis. while booth’s sunny demeanor fits perfectly with the southern theme of root & bone, she was born and raised in perth, australia. growing up in a family of restaurant owners, it was the backyard barbeques of booth’s childhood that taught her the power of food to bring people together. it was mcinnis, with his childhood spent on his grandparents’ alabama farm, and his culinary training in charleston, south carolina, who ignited booth’s reverence for southern fare. 
combine two barbecue experts who recognize the joy that comes from breaking bread with good company and you get the ultimate comfort meal in manhattan’s lower east side. 
to see my full interview and shoot with janine, head to electrifymag.com. link in profile.

text:
this is outfit 9 of the #10x10challenge and can you believe this is a dress?! well it is, and i tucked that mofo straight into my pants. ⠀
⠀
one of the reasons why i love doing these challenges is because they inspire creativity to think of new and unusual ways to style your existing clothes. i never would have thought of this before, but i ended up loving the look. ⠀
⠀
also i'm calling this my new "power stance". over the course of the past few weeks i've had an awakening. i am awake to the fact that in order to see the changes i want to see, i cannot let others do the work for me. if i don't speak up then i am complicit. ⠀
⠀
i've had 2 instances in the past 2 days where a man (a stranger in one case, acquaintance in the other case) tried to speak to me as if i only existed as an ornament specifically designed to be hung on a tree, to be gawked at and admired by men. normally i would be polite and meekly say "thank you" and move on with my day. but not this time. i'm done and i'm tired. this time i stood up for myself, used my voice, my words. one of them i explained calmly (as it was in front of co-workers) that the way they spoke to me was wrong, and then other one was sort of ripped a new one. ⠀
⠀
i am done with being weak. i am done with being taken advantage of. i am done with being seen as a face and body, but not a mind, a well of creativity and humor and ambition and inner thoughts. i am bigger than the way that i look. i will use my words to fight you, to disarm you, to make you uncomfortable. and in the end, i will have the power-- not you.

text:
daily song — elected, alice cooper (1974)
.
there comes a time when you say “enough is enough.” for me, that time came in november 2016.
.
i’ve been politically aware all my adult life. i follow the issues and candidates, and vote in practically every election. i’ve contributed from time to time. the first check i ever wrote to a presidential candidate was barack obama in 2008.
.
but i had never volunteered. never made phone calls. never hosted a fundraiser. then donald trump happened — and everything changed. if any good has come from his presidency, it’s that people have been galvanized. the women’s march. the #metoo movement. and here in oklahoma, the teachers’ strike.
.
count me among those who pledged to be more involved. about a year ago, i marked my calendar to take vacation on november 6 of this year, to help our candidates. i’ll wave signs, drive people to the polls, make phone calls. whatever is needed.
.
today i got a warm-up. i spent three hours volunteering for kendra horn, democrat for the u.s. fifth congressional district. my part was easy. i drove, while a nice woman named marguerite, an officer with the state’s democratic party, knocked on doors. it was great.
.
come tuesday, i’ll drop luke at school, then spend the day volunteering for our candidates. we’ll hit a few watch parties that night. win or lose, at least we won’t have sat on the sidelines.
.
@alicecooper #gotv #midterms #election2018 #music #musicblogger #oklahoma #democrat #classicrock
.
(for the music and more, follow the link in the bio.)

text:
last year on this date i was awarded something unexpected that brought me to my knees. it was program for aid to victims of sexual assault (pavsa) community ally of the year 😭 they honored me with a beautiful plaque and a chance to speak and share my story and a few songs. ♥️
.
many of you have heard this story but i was sexually assaulted in 2006. it was post college where i had even received trainings in sexual assault victim advocacy and self defense and domestic violence survivor advocacy. i had been flying high off of my first artist residency.  i did everything "safe" and yet it still happened.  while i did report it the day after due to the urging of my friends (he got a petty misdemeanor) i fell pretty silent about it. i struggled in confidence (always had), and relationships. had nightmares.got therapy and emdr and kinda tried to escape by moving around a lot. ♥️
.
finally in 2016 i wrote my song "petty misdemeanor" bemoaning the tiny charge compared to the trauma i had to move through.  i recorded it on 2017's "the majesty of beasts" ep and still donate a portion of sales of this album to pavsa.  this award meant so much to me, and i even said then that it meant more than a grammy (though i hope for one of those, ha!) ... it meant so much to know that my struggles are not in vain and we can fight this beast that is power and control, domination and hate,  by coming together and sharing our stories. ♥️
.
this is a timely memory because it is time to vote on tuesday.  vote with your heart. we can't have predators holding court.  vote for compassion and humanity.  vote for the voiceless and those who survive what many of us choose to turn a blind eye to.  vote with love.  thank you. ♥️
.

#metoo #vote #survivor #sexualassault #pavsa #compassion 
pic: lindsy wayt
video of the songs i shared at the event here: https://youtu.be/xntdzjk9cs8

text:
persephone’s dancer rising (base only)
hand-carved alabaster stone

even more progress... and more... and more... and more and more... her face is beginning to shape and state back.

this part of the piece, the base, is a conglomeration of ancient goddess forms from throughout our ancestral past, rising up to hold the phoenix wing aloft. 
in process, a few more details and i have only 5 more days to go. 
this piece is meant as a trophy of triumph, a modern nike, presented to all women who have endured, (silently, painfully, sometimes with strength, other times with weakness, always courageously, and always without expressed informed consent) sexual assault.
it represents your futures beyond this era (that could end tomorrow or next year but certainly within your lifetime). it is the triumph that is inevitable for all women.
